        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 3:19AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 319 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 7 miles northeast of Adrian to 5 miles north of
Wildorado to 4 miles west of Mescalero Park. Movement was northeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vega, Amarillo, Mescalero Park, Bushland, Lake Tanglewood,
Timbercreek Canyon, Adrian, Valley De Oro, Canyon, Umbarger,
Wildorado, and Palo Duro Canyon.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 27 between mile markers 95 and 123.
Interstate 40 between mile markers 17 and 80.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
